SIMPLE: leakage
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Leakage
<hw>Leak"age</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. D.
<ets>lekkage</ets>, for sense 1.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A leaking;
also, the quantity that enters or issues by leaking.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Com.)</fld> <def>An allowance of a certain rate per
cent for the leaking of casks, or waste of liquors by leaking.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>A <er>leak{3}</er>; also; the
quantity of electricity thus wasted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Leakiness</ent>⟦br⟧
